s%20its%20Joe-Joe's%20or%20Cookie%20Butter.%20That%20wasn't%20always%20the%20case%20%E2%80%94%20its%20White%20Cheddar%20Corn%20Puffs%20had%20more%20sodium%20than%20the%20Pirate's%20Booty%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20small%20nutritional%20differences%20rarely%20outweigh%20overall%20dietary%20patterns.%20Maddie%20Pasquariello%2C%20a%20registered%20dietitian%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20if%20you're%20mostly%20cooking%20meals%20from%20whole%20foods%2C%20being%20mindful%20of%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flower-blood-pressure-cut-back-on-salt-super-effective-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esodium%20intake%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20eating%20minimal%20UPFs%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20fixate%20on%20ultraprocessed%20labels%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20ethos%20with%20nutrition%20is%20that%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20the%20chips%20or%20the%20brownie%2C%20have%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20be%20fun%20to%20seek%20out%20healthier%20versions%20of%20your%20favorite%20foods%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20you%20need%20to%20treat%20your%20whole%20diet%20like%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1692ebf-0046-40d5-aa2c-33f63e05d26e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20fewer%20additives%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20healthier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224992%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Grocery%20store%20chips%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69657a2c764ca5f34d2a4fe1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdditives%20can%20make%20ultraprocessed%20foods%20more%20shelf-stable%20and%20palatable.%3Cp%3EJames%20Leynse%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20comparison%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20how%20many%20ingredients%20each%20product%20had%2C%20and%20which%20of%20those%20ingredients%20were%20additives%3A%20ingredients%20which%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20may%20be%20used%20to%20bind%20an%20ultraprocessed%20food%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20clear%2C%20ingredients%20like%20riboflavin%20(vitamin%20B2)%20or%20ascorbic%20acid%20(derived%20from%20vitamin%20C)%20are%20not%20harmful%20on%20their%20own%3B%20they%20are%20essential%20nutrients.%20The%20issue%20isn't%20their%20presence%3B%20it's%20what%20their%20presence%20often%20signals%20about%20how%20much%20a%20food%20has%20been%20processed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20compounds%20are%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Ffood-additives%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadded%20back%20to%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20processing%20to%20stabilize%20texture%2C%20prevent%20spoilage%2C%20and%20replace%20nutrients%20lost%20during%20refining.%20They%20can%20be%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20original%20food%20structure%20has%20been%20compromised%20during%20processing%2C%20stripping%20away%20fiber%20and%20micronutrients%20that%20contribute%20to%20the%20food's%20texture%20and%20flavor.%20Additives%20are%20used%20to%20make%20packaged%20products%20palatable%20and%20shelf-stable%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditives%20alone%20aren't%20what%20make%20UPFs%20less%20nutritious%2C%20Pasquariello%20said.%20What%20matters%20more%20is%20the%20overall%20macronutrient%20profile%20%E2%80%94%20how%20much%20protein%20or%20fiber%20the%20food%20has%2C%20if%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20palatable%20the%20food%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%2C%20how%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20overeat%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BMany%20UPFs%20are%20highly%20palatable%2C%20making%20it%20more%20likely%20that%20you%20over-consume%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultra-processed-food-expert-tips-for-avoiding-the-worst-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EResearch%20links%20ultraprocessed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20type%202%20diabetes%2C%20and%20weight%20gain%2C%20among%20other%20health%20issues.%20These%20risks%20show%20up%20across%20brands%2C%20including%20the%20ones%20advertising%20%26quot%3Ball-natural%26quot%3B%20ingredients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283c52a6c-07ca-43bc-885c-7e664066a2c8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20Trader%20Joe's%20does%20stand%20out%3A%20price%20and%20marketing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224505%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trader%20Joe's%20snack%20mix%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69657ad504eda4732f2ef09c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223379%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETrader%20Joe's%20products%20tended%20to%20make%20fewer%20misleading%20health%20claims.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETrader%20Joe's%20often%20wins%20on%20price%2C%20sometimes%20dramatically.%20Its%20Pretzel%20Slims%2C%20frozen%20pizza%2C%20and%20frozen%20butter%20chicken%20were%20all%20about%20half%20the%20price%20of%20its%20competitors'%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20stood%20out%20in%20its%20marketing.%20Pasquariello%20said%20a%20lot%20of%20brands%20put%20labels%20like%20%26quot%3Blow-calorie%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20in%20fiber%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bgood%20source%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Borganic%26quot%3B%20on%20their%20packaging%2C%20which%20she%20%26quot%3Bultimately%20ignores%26quot%3B%20until%20she's%20read%20the%20label.%20Overall%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrader-joes-how-gets-you-spend-money-psychologist-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrader%20Joe's%20marketing%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20simpler%2C%20with%20fewer%20health%20claims%20on%20the%20packaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20caveat%20was%20its%20serving%20sizes%3A%20On%20some%20products%2C%20like%20its%20Joe-Joe's%2C%20Trader%20Joe's%20used%20a%20smaller%20serving%20size%20than%20its%20competitor%2C%20making%20it%20appear%20overall%20lower%20in%20calories%20or%20fat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221dd0039a-b9b9-4a8b-81e7-7fc8ab040bc1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bottom%20line%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20this%20ad-hoc%20comparison%2C%20Trader%20Joe's%20foods%20are%20sometimes%20marginally%20better%20than%20other%20brands%20in%20terms%20of%20sodium%20levels.%20Often%2C%20its%20packaged%20snacks%20are%20nutritionally%20similar%20to%20those%20found%20at%20other%20major%20supermarkets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20snacks%20are%20still%20snacks%20and%20should%20be%20eaten%20in%20moderation.%20The%20biggest%20health%20gains%20come%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fold-food-pyramid-vs-new-rfk-1980-1992-myplate-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eminimally%20processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20whole%20grains%2C%20and%20legumes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20eating%20all%20that%2C%20choosing%20between%20a%20Joe-Joe%20and%20an%20Oreo%20comes%20down%20to%20preference.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EWhen%20reached%20for%20comment%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20from%20Trader%20Joe's%20shared%20the%20following%2C%20which%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BTrader%20Joe's-branded%20products%20promise%20great%20quality%20for%20exceptional%2C%20everyday%20prices.%20At%20Trader%20Joe's%2C%20value%20lies%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20top%20quality%20and%20great%20price.%20We%20taste%20everything%20before%20we%20put%20our%20name%20on%20it%20and%20offer%20only%20what%20we%20feel%20is%20extraordinary.%20We%20are%20grateful%20to%20each%20customer%20who%20chooses%20to%20shop%20in%20our%20stores%20and%20value%20the%20trust%20they%20place%20in%20our%20brand%20every%20time%20they%20shop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-trader-joes-healthi